               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]] has notes on p. 152 and translates on pp. 151-152: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 He did ... the bodhisatva ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 The voice of Brahma, ... adorned in the eight ways ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 The most excellent patience is the jewel there. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 the Buddha. Through what means are the thirty two signs ... to be attained? The eighty ornaments ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a5 Having become the most excellent ornament of all this world. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a6 [in this way] the thirty two signs/marks are to be [attained]. The eighty ornaments/anuvyañjana ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 looked at the Maitreya, this balance of omniscience, with insatiable blue [eyes] &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 Whereby immediately [and] always proportionately the Buddha epochs would never fail &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 Thereupon [he] trusts in Maitreya. He who as the good gift of the dharma gives bones ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 comes together with the Buddha in [his] turn. 8. Again Maitreya [making the] añjali [gesture with his hands] ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b5 Let him be careful! The best, the sage, and the skilled &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b6 Lotus-coloured the Buddha spoke together with Maitreya. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translations from [[Adams, 2DoT]]:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;a5&lt;/b&gt; "having been this excellent jewel for the whole world" [545-546]&lt;/p&gt;</item>
